main event: Multiple unidentified objects were observed at Pease AFB, New Hampshire on August 20, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar and visually observed by control tower personnel., The objects were described as a high-speed moving aircraft and a low altitude slow moving light., Three Air Force personnel reported the sighting from the control tower., The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes., The objects exhibited unusual flight characteristics, which led to them being classified as 'unexplained'.
sighted object: irregular shaped light, mostly round, white with occasional red shading
witness description: Air Force personnel including airmen and a station weather observer
